  url "https://en.wiktionary.org/w/api.php?action=parse&page=thank_you&prop=wikitext&formatversion=2&format=json&redirects=1"
  body "ter. \""I Love you&nbsp;… For all the right reasons,\"" he wrote. \""And I'm glad 2 know u feel the true love u have 4 me again&nbsp;… '''Thank u'''!! You make me feel like i really am superman!!\""}}\n#*"
  body " {{quote-book|en|author=[[w:Roy Williams (playwright)|Roy Williams]]|title=Kingston 14|location=London; New York, N.Y.|publisher=[[w:Bloomsbury Publishing|Bloomsbury Methuen Drama]]|year=2014|section="
  body "act II|page=71|isbn=978-1-4725-8826-5|passage=''Adrian'' Shush. / ''Carl'' '''Thank yu'''. / ''Adrian'' Fer what? / ''Carl'' Fer staying. / ''Adrian'' Man tell mi to. Nuh thank mi. But you must shush."
  body "}}\n# {{senseid|en|acceptance of an offer}} {{lb|en|often|with ''[[yes]]''}} {{non-gloss|Used as a polite affirmative to accept an offer.}}\n#: {{nearsyn|en|please<id:acceptance of an offer>}}\n#: {{u"
  body "x|en|—May I help you? —Yes, '''thank you'''.}}\n#: {{ux|en|—May I help you? —'''Thank you'''.}}\n# {{ng|A polite [[dismissal]]; usually used in [[professional]] contexts.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author="
  body "Amy Andrews|title=Limbo|location=Sydney, N.S.W.|publisher=Escape Publishing|year=2015|isbn=978-0-85799-250-5|passage=‘No, come in,’ he said. ‘Martin, right? Have a seat.’ {{...}} ‘'''Thank you''', no,"
  body " I won’t.’ He moved inside a little more.}}\n\n====Usage notes====\nCan also be used in response to an offer not accepted, as if standing for [[no thank you]]. For example, someone offered a bowl full"
  body " of strawberries after having already eaten a hearty meal might respond with ''I'm full, '''thank you'''.''\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{l|en|thank u}} {{qualifier|[[eye dialect]], chiefly Intern"
  body "et slang}}\n* {{l|en|thank ya}} {{qualifier|slang}}\n* {{l|en|thank ye}} {{qualifier|archaic}}\n* {{l|en|sank you}} {{qualifier|non-native}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|en|cheers}} {{qualifier|informal"
  body "}}\n* {{l|en|much appreciated}}\n* {{l|en|gracias}}\n* {{l|en|gramercy}} {{qualifier|archaic}}\n* {{l|en|much obliged}}\n* {{l|en|ta}} {{qualifier|Australia|Britain|New Zealand}}\n* {{l|en|thank you v"
  body "ery much}}\n* {{l|en|thanks}}, {{l|en|thanks a bunch}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{l|en|thanks a lot}}, {{l|en|thanks a million}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{l|en|thanks very much}}\n* {{l|en|ty}} {{quali"
  body "fier|Internet|text messaging}}\n* ''See also'' [[Thesaurus:thank you]]\n* ''See also'' [[you're welcome]], a typical reply\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|I'm fine, thank you|no thank you|thank-you"
