  body "* Telugu: {{tt+|te|ధన్యవాదాలు}}\n* Thai: {{tt+|th|ขอบคุณ}}\n*: Northern Thai: {{t-needed|nod}}\n* Tibetan: {{tt|bo|ཐུགས་རྗེ་ཆེ}}\n* Tigrinya: {{tt|ti|የቐንየለይ}}, {{tt|ti|የመስግነካ}}\n* Tlingit: {{tt|tli|gu"
  body "nalchéesh}}\n* Tok Pisin: {{tt|tpi|tenkyu}}\n* Tokelauan: {{t|tkl|fakafetai}}\n* Tongan: {{tt|to|mālō}}\n* Tswana: {{tt|tn|ke a leboga}}\n* Turkish: {{tt|tr|sağ olun}} {{qualifier|formal}}, {{tt+|tr|s"
  body "ağ ol}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{tt+|tr|teşekkür ederim}}, {{tt+|tr|teşekkürler}}, {{tt+|tr|mersi}}\n* Turkmen: {{tt|tk|sag boluň}}, {{tt|tk|spasiba}}\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|tk|саг болуң}}\n* Tuvan: {{tt"
  body "|tyv|улуг өөрдүм}}, {{tt|tyv|четтирдим}}\n* Tz'utujil: {{t-check|tzj|maltiox}}\n* Udihe: {{tt|ude|асаса|tr=asasa}}\n* Udmurt: {{tt|udm|тау}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|дя́кую}} {{q|from one speaker}}, {{t"
  body "t|uk|дя́куємо}} {{q|from more than one speaker}}, {{tt+|uk|спаси́бі}}\n* Unami: {{tt|unm|wanìshi}}\n* Urdu: {{tt+|ur|شُکْرِیَہ}}, {{tt|ur|جَزاک اَللٰہ}} {{qualifier|often used by Muslims}}, {{tt|ur|دَ"
  body "ھنْیَہ واد}} {{qualifier|used by Hindus}}, {{tt|ur|جَزاک اَللٰہ خَیر}} {{qualifier|often used by Muslims}}, {{tt|ur|نَوازِش}} {{qualifier|formal}}, {{tt|ur|مِہْرْبانی}}\n* Uyghur: {{tt|ug|رەھمەت}}, {{"
  body "tt|ug|ھەشقاللا}}\n* Uzbek: {{tt+|uz|rahmat}}, {{tt+|uz|tashakkur}}\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|uz|рахмат}}\n* Venetan: {{t|vec|grassie}}\n* Veps: {{tt|vep|kitän}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|cám ơn}} ({{tt|vi|感恩}}"
  body ") (''plus one of:'' {{tt+|vi|ông}}, {{l|vi|bà}}, {{l|vi|cô}}, {{l|vi|anh}}, {{tt+|vi|chị}}, {{l|vi|em}}, {{tt|vi|quí vị}} &ndash; ''depending on subject of gratitude''), {{tt+|vi|cảm ơn}}\n* Võro: {{t"
  body "t|vro|aiteh}}\n* Waigali: {{tt|wbk|ṣëṣü bü}}\n* Walloon: {{tt+|wa|merci}}, {{tt+|wa|gråces}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|diolch}}\n* Wolof: {{tt|wo|jéréjëf}}\n* Xhosa: {{tt|xh|enkosi}}\n* Yakut: {{tt|sah|баһыы"
  body "ба}}, {{tt|sah|махтал}} {{qualifier|formal}}\n* Yiddish: {{tt|yi|אַ דאַנק}}, {{tt|yi|אַ דאַנק דיר}}, {{t|yi|שכּ׳ח|tr=shkoyekh}}\n* Yoruba: {{tt|yo|ẹ ṣé}} {{qualifier|formal}}, {{tt|yo|ẹ ṣeun}} {{quali"
  body "fier|formal}}, {{tt|yo|o ṣé}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{tt|yo|o ṣeun}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n* Yucatec Maya: {{t|yua|níib óolal}}\n* Yup'ik: {{tt|esu|quyana}}\n* Zazaki: {{tt|zza|teşekur kenam}}\n* "
  body "Zhuang: {{tt|za|dwgrengz mwngz loz|lit=you worked hard}}\n* Zulu: {{tt+|zu|ngiyabonga}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{alternative spelling of|en|thank-you}}.\n\n===Further re"
  body "ading===\n* {{cite-web|author=Jennifer Runner|title=‘Thank you’ in more than 465 languages|url=http://users.elite.net/runner/jennifers/thankyou.htm|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/2016102121005"
  body "4/http://users.elite.net/runner/jennifers/thankyou.htm|archivedate=21 October 2016|work=Jennifer's Language Pages&nbsp;– Greetings in More Than 3000 Languages|date=14 August 2016}}.\n\n{{cln|en|expres"
  body "sions of gratitude}}\n\n==Chinese==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|zh|thank Q|thank q|thankq}}\n* {{alt|zh|thank橋|fan橋|釘橋|頂轎}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|yue|en|thank you}}.\n\n===Pronunciation=="
  body "=\n{{zh-pron\n|c=feng1 kiu4,fen1 kiu4,deng1 kiu4\n|cat=v\n}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|zh|verb}}\n\n# {{lb|zh|Hong Kong Cantonese|sometimes|humorous}} to [[thank]]; to be [[grateful]] to\n#: {{zh-x|'''@t{"
  body "}h{}a{}n{feng1}k{}&#032;@y{}o{}u{kiu4}''' 你|'''thank''' you|C}}\n#* {{quote-av|yue|year=2000|title=w:War of the Genders|actor=w:Dayo Wong|role=Lok}}\n#*: {{zh-x|'''@t{f}h{}a{e}nk{g1}&#032;y{k}o{i}u{u4"
  body "-1}''' @&#032; y{j}o{u}u{1} 啦，一於 噉 話，@t{f}h{}a{e}nk{g1}&#032;y{ki}o{u}u{4}&#032;t{f}h{}a{e}nk{g1}&#032;y{ki}o{u}u{4}|'''Thank''' you very much, that's how it'll be. Thanks, thanks.|C|inline=0}}\n#* {{"
  body "quote-song|yue|text=I am vely vely vely vely vely vely '''thank q''' you / '''Thank q''' you love my black skin shoes / I love your ball shoes too / {{…}} / I am rely rely rely rely rely rely '''thank"
  body " q''' you / '''Thank&#032;q''' you love my left door tooth / I love your wine 凹 too|t=I am extremely '''grateful''' to you / '''Thank''' you for loving my black leather shoes / I love your sneakers to"
  body "o / {{…}} / I am really '''grateful''' to you / '''Thank''' you for loving my left incisor / I love your dimples too|year=2017|artist=Dickson|publisher=w:TVMost|title=Earth vely danger|trans-title=Ear"
  body "th is very dangerous|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4NDPDlaW7js}}\n#* {{quote-song|yue|text=I'm fine '''thank橋''' u|t=I'm fine, '''thank''' you|year=2021|artist=w:Serrini|lyricist=w:Serrini|title"
  body "=I'm fine, thx|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7dlUmEXAjks}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|yue|多謝}}\n* {{l|yue|唔該}}""}}"

