  body " Turkish: {{t|ota|مرسی|tr=mersi|id=thanks}}\n* Turkmen: {{t|tk|sagboluň}}, {{t|tk|spasiba}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|дя́кую}}, {{t+|uk|спаси́бі}}\n* Unami: {{t|unm|wanìshi}}\n* Urdu: {{t+|ur|شُکْرِیَہ}},"
  body " {{t|ur|نَوَازِش}},  {{t|ur|مِہَرْبانی|tr=meharbānī}}, {{t|ur|دھنیہ واد|tr=dhanya-vād}} ''(rarely by Hindus)''\n* Uyghur: {{t|ug|رەھمەت}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|rahmat}}, {{t+|uz|tashakkur}}\n* Vietnamese:"
  body " {{t+|vi|cám ơn}} ({{t|vi|感恩}}) (''plus one of:'' [[ông]], [[bà#Vietnamese|bà]], [[cô#Vietnamese|cô]], [[anh#Vietnamese|anh]], [[chị]], [[em#Vietnamese|em]], [[quí vị]] &ndash; ''depending on subject "
  body "of gratitude'')\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|diolch}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|דאַנק}}\n* Yucatec Maya: {{t|yua|níib óol}}\n* Yup'ik: {{t|esu|quyana}}\n* Zulu: {{t+|zu|ngiyabonga}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-to"
