  url "https://en.wiktionary.org/w/api.php?action=parse&page=tomato&prop=wikitext&formatversion=2&format=json&redirects=1"
  body "{""parse"":{""title"":""tomato"",""pageid"":3607,""redirects"":[],""wikitext"":""{{also|tomàto|tōmato|tōm̧ato}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n[[File:Tomato Solanum lycopersicum (15806140083).jpg|thumb|a tomato ({{senseno|"
  body "en|Q23501}})]]\n[[File:Tomato.jpg|thumb|a tomato ({{senseno|en|Q20638126}})]]\n[[File:Lufa Farms Beefsteak Tomato.jpg|thumb|a sliced tomato ({{senseno|en|Q20638126}}) next to a whole one]]\n\n===Alter"
  body "native forms===\n* {{alter|en|tomatoe||archaic|now|nonstandard}}\n* {{alter|en|tomater||eye dialect}}\n* {{alter|en|'mater||Southern US|Appalachia|informal}}\n\n===Etymology===\nVariant of earlier {{m"
  body "|en|tomate}}, from {{bor|en|es|tomate}}, from {{der|en|nci|tomatl}}, from {{der|en|azc-nah-pro|*toma-|*toma-tl}}. Compare {{m|es|tomatillo}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/təˈmɑː.təʊ/|a=RP,AU}}\"
  body "n** {{audio|en|en-uk-tomato.ogg|a=UK|IPA=[tʰə̥ˈmɑːtʰəʉ̯]}}\n** {{audio|en|En-au-tomato.ogg|a=AU|IPA=[tʰə̥ˈmɐːtʰɐʉ̯]}}\n* {{IPA|en|/təˈmeɪ.toʊ/|a=US}}, {{q|colloquial, sometimes}} {{IPAchar|/təˈmeɪ.tə/"
  body "}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-tomato.ogg|a=California}}\n* {{IPA|en|[tʰəˈmeɪɾo]|[tʰəˈme(ː)to(ː)]|[tʰɵ-]|[-ma-]|a=CA}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ʈɵˈmaʈo/|/ʈɵˈmɑʈo/|/ʈɵˈmeʈo/|a=Indic}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɑːtəʊ|eɪtəʊ|ætəʊ|s=3}"
  body "}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|~|es}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q23501}} A widely [[cultivated]] [[plant]], {{taxfmt|Solanum lycopersicum|species}}, having [[edible]] [[fruit]].\n# {{senseid|en|Q20638126}} The sa"
  body "vory [[fruit]] of this plant, most often red when ripe, treated as a [[vegetable]] in [[horticulture]] and [[cooking]].\n#: {{ux|en| He was chopping a '''tomato''' to put in the salad.}}\n#: {{ux|en| "
  body "He was eating a '''tomato''' when his boss called him.}}\n#: {{syn|en|golden apple|q1=archaic|love apple|q2=archaic|wolf's peach|q3=obsolete|tomater|mato|mater}}\n#: {{meronyms|en|lycopene}}\n#* '''19"
  body "90''', ''JSG Trading Corp. v. Tray-Wrap, Inc.'', 917 F.2d 75 (2d Cir. 1990)\n#*: In common parlance '''tomatoes''' are vegetables, as the Supreme Court observed long ago [see ''Nix v. Hedden'' 149 U.S"
  body ". 304, 307, 13 S.Ct. 881, 882, 37 L.Ed. 745 (1893)], although botanically speaking they are actually a fruit. [''26 Encyclopedia Americana'' 832 (Int'l. ed. 1981)]. Regardless of classification, peopl"
  body "e have been enjoying '''tomatoes''' for centuries; even Mr. Pickwick, as Dickens relates, ate his chops in \""tomata\"" sauce.\n# {{senseid|en|Q6592940}} A shade of [[red]], the colour typical of a ripe"
  body " tomato.\n#: {{color panel|FF6347}}\n# {{senseid|en|physically attractive woman}} {{lb|en|slang}} An attractive [[woman]].\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=April 4, 1999|author=Frank Decaro|authorlink=Fran"
  body "k DeCaro|title=No Longer the Punch-Line State|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1999/04/04/style/no-longer-punch-line-state-lauryn-hill-sopranos-others-are-unapologetic-new.html|sect"
  body "ion=9|page=1|text=Deborah Harry, the New Wave goddess, is finally admitting -- after all the peroxide and posturing of the 1970's and 80's -- that she's really just a <nowiki>''</nowiki>'''tomato'''<n"
  body "owiki>''</nowiki> (her word) from Paterson {{...}}.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2008|author=Denny Durbin|title=Lazy Enchiladas: Redefining Success: Tasty Lessons on Love, Life, & Relationships|publishe"
  body "r=Bodega Publishing|isbn=9780980207248|page=13\n|passage=When she left the room, I asked Robert, “Who&#39;s the '''tomato'''?” “Marisa. She&#39;s from Mexico.” He had a telltale smile on his face.}}\n"
  body "#* '''2015''' [https://www.bustle.com/articles/116384-19-old-fashioned-compliments-we-should-bring-back 19 Old-Fashioned Compliments We Should Bring Back]\n#*: That shirt makes you look like such a gl"
  body "orious '''tomato'''.\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2020|author=Libba Bray|title=The King of Crows|publisher=Little, Brown Books for Young Readers|isbn=9780316532624\n|passage=“Who&#39;s the '''tomato'''?” "
  body "a cop said as Evie walked past. “Her? She&#39;s the stiff&#39;s niece,” another cop answered.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2025|author={{w|Thomas Pynchon}}|title=Shadow Ticket|publisher=Jonathan Cape|pa"
  body "ge=19|passage=When did this happen last, a '''tomato''' he's hardly met going to so much trouble? Ever?}}\n# {{lb|en|slang}} A stupid act or person.\n\n====Hypernyms====\n* [[Thesaurus:fruit|fruit]], "
  body "[[Thesaurus:vegetable|vegetable]] ''(see [[w:tomato#Fruit or vegetable|tomato § Fruit or vegetable]]'')\n** {{l|en|berry}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|clamato|pomato|potomato|Sacratomato|tomacc"
