  body "tive===\n{{en-adj}}\n\n# Of a shade of [[red]], the colour of a ripe tomato.\n#: {{color panel|FF6347}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=w:Beverley Farmer|chapter=December|chapterurl=https://books.google.co"
  body "m/books?id=n3n-DwAAQBAJ&pg=PT251|title=A Body of Water|location=Sydney, N.S.W.|publisher=w:Giramondo Publishing|year=1990|year_published=2020|isbn=978-1-925818-25-3|passage=Her face is on the cover: t"
  body "he Anne Estelle Rice portrait – or the black-eyed Japanese-bobbed head-and-shoulders bit of it – and the square-yoked dress is '''tomato''', or pomegranate, but ''never'' persimmon. If it stayed too l"
  body "ong in the sun and faded, well yes, maybe then…}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Jackie Braun|chapter=Most Focused|title=Mr. Right There All Along|series=Harlequin Romance, #4258; The Fun Factor|location="
  body "Toronto, Ont.|publisher=[[w:Harlequin Enterprises|Harlequin]]|year=2011|page=220|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/mrrighttherealla0000brau/page/220/mode/1up|isbn=978-0-373-74117-5|passage=And she’d"
  body " slathered a heavy layer of foundation over the raw skin of her face with the end result being a complexion that was more '''tomato''' than orange.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Jillian Cantor|title=Ma"
  body "rgot|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=w:Riverhead Books|year=2013|pages=[https://archive.org/details/margot0000cant_s1j4/page/93/mode/1up 93–94] (chapter 16) and [https://archive.org/details/margot00"
  body "00cant_s1j4/page/164/mode/1up 164] (chapter 26)|isbn=978-1-59448-643-2|passage=This afternoon, though, she saunters in, draped in a dress the color of a ripe tomato, with a hat to match, her hair twis"
  body "ted underneath in some kind of fashionable up-do that seems impossible to create oneself. {{...}} Penny is sitting there, on the bed, next to me, chewing on the end of the pen, dressed in her frivolou"
  body "s '''tomato''' dress.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Traci Andrighetti|chapter=9|chapterurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=-ypeEAAAQBAJ&pg=PT130|title=Valpolicella Violet|series=Franki Amato Mysterie"
  body "s|seriesvolume=7|publisher=Limoncello Press|year=2021|isbn=978-1-7355761-9-0|passage=Intending to tease out Shona’s know-it-all nature by spouting off some trivia, I googled the Pala d’Oro on my phone"
  body ". It was pure folly, but I was kind of worried about her. “Wikipedia says the cloth has a hundred and eighty-seven enamel plaques depicting Christ and the saints that are decorated with gold, silver, "
  body "and around two thousand gems.” I peeked at Shona, whose face was '''tomato''', and continued.}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|of the color of a ripe tomato}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|[[tomaatti|tomaa"
  body "tin]][[punainen]]}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive|rare}} to [[pelt]] with tomatoes\n# {{lb|en|transitive|rare}} to add tomatoes to (a dish)\n\n{{cln|en|nouns wit"
  body "h irregular plurals}}\n{{c|en|Fruits|Tomatoes|Vegetables}}\n\n==Amis==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|ami|ja|-}} {{ja-r|トマト}}, from {{der|ami|en|tomato}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|ami|noun}}\n\n# [[#English|"
  body "tomato]]\n\n===References===\n* {{R:ami:Dictionary of the Central Dialect of Amis|537900}}\n\n{{topic|ami|Fruits|Nightshades|Vegetables}}\n\n==Chichewa==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|ny|en|"
  body "tomato}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{ny-IPA|tomáto}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ny-noun|tomáto|1a|-}}\n\n# {{l|en|tomato}}\n#: {{syn|ny|phwetekere|matimati}}\n\n{{topics|ny|Fruits}}\n\n==Esperanto==\n{{wp|eo:}"
  body "}\n[[Image:Bright red tomato and cross section02.jpg|thumb|right]]\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|eo|ru|томат}}, {{der|eo|de|Tomate}}, {{der|eo|en|tomato}}, {{der|eo|fr|tomate}}, all from {{der|eo|es|"
  body "tomate}}, from {{der|eo|nci|tomatl}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{eo-pr|a=LL-Q143 (epo)-Robin van der Vliet-tomato.wav;LL-Q143 (epo)-Lepticed7-tomato.wav}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{eo-head}}\n\n# {{l|en|tomato}"
  body "} {{gl|fruit}}\n# tomato plant {{gl|{{taxfmt|Solanum lycopersicum|species}}}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|eo|tomata|pos=a|t=made of or related to tomatoes}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:eo:PIV "
  body "2020}}\n* {{R:eo:ReVo}}\n\n{{c|eo|Fruits|Vegetables|Tomatoes}}\n\n==Iban==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|iba|en|tomato}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|iba|/tomato/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head"
  body "|iba|noun}}\n\n# {{l|en|tomato}}\n\n{{c|iba|Fruits|Vegetables}}\n\n==Ido==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{io-IPA}}\n* {{rhymes|io|ato}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{io-noun|tomat}}\n\n# {{l|en|tomato}}\n\n{{C|io|Foo"
  body "ds}}\n\n==Italian==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|it|tomate}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|it|:bor|en:tomato}}\n{{bor+|it|en|tomato}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|it|LL-Q652 (ita)-DanielParol"
  body "iere-tomato.wav}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{it-noun|m}}\n\n# {{lb|it|rare}} {{l|en|tomato}}\n#: {{syn|it|pomodoro}}\n# {{lb|it|informal}} {{l|en|ketchup}}\n\n==Japanese==\n\n===Romanization===\n{{ja-romaji}}\n"
  body "\n# {{ja-romanization of|トマト}}\n\n==Swahili==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|sw|en|tomato}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|sw|Sw-ke-tomato.flac|a=Kenya}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sw-noun|n}}\n\n# [[#English|t"
  body "omato]]\n#: {{syn|sw|nyanya}}\n#* {{quote-web|sw|date=16 December 2021|work=BBC News Swahili|url=https://www.bbc.com/swahili/habari-59678736|title=Wakenya wapata faraja mashambani baada ya corona kuwa"
  body "timua mjini|text=Alianza kilimo cha malenge, mtama, '''tomato''' na sukuma wiki - na sasa anauza bidhaa zake katika soko la nyumbani.|t=He started cultivating pumpkin, millet, '''tomato''' and sukuma "
  body "wiki - and now he sells his products in the domestic market.}}\n\n{{C|sw|Vegetables}}\n\n==Tok Pisin==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|tpi|en|tomato}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|tpi|noun}}\n\n# {{l|en|toma"
  body "to}}\n#* {{quote-book\n|tpi\n|year=1995\n|author=John Verhaar\n|title=Toward a reference grammar of Tok Pisin: an experiment in corpus linguistics\n|chapter=\n|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=4De"
  body "KkIzS8B4C&pg=PA433#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|isbn=0-8248-1672-2\n|page=433\n|passage=Mekim olsem pinis, orait tupela i planim taro na banana, na kumu, painap, kon, '''tomato''', na kaukau tu.}}\n\n{{c|tpi"
  body "|Fruits|Nightshades|Vegetables}}\n\n==Welsh==\n{{swp|cy:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|cy|en|tomato}}, from {{der|cy|es|tomate}}, from {{der|cy|nci|tomatl}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|cy|/tɔˈmatɔ"
  body "/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{cy-noun|m|tomatoes}}\n\n# {{l|en|tomato}}\n#: {{syn|cy|afal cariad}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|cy|tomato bach melys|t=cherry tomato}}\n\n===Mutation===\n{{cy-mut}}\n\n===Fur"
  body "ther reading===\n* {{R:cy:GPC}}\n\n{{c|cy|Fruits|Nightshades|Vegetables}}""}}"

