  body "{""parse"":{""title"":""water"",""pageid"":3749998,""redirects"":[],""wikitext"":""{{also|wáter|wàter|Water}}\n==English==\n{{wp|<dab>}}\n[[File:Stilles Mineralwasser.jpg|thumb|A glass of '''water''' ({{senseno|en"
  body "|Q283}})]]\n[[File:H2O 2D labelled.svg|thumb|A '''water''' molecule]]\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{a|en|GA}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈwɔ.tɚ/|[ˈwɔ.ɾɚ]|a=non-cot-caught}}\n*** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Nail123Real"
  body "-water.wav|a=US,non-cot-caught}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈwɑ.tɚ/|[ˈwɑ.ɾɚ]|/ˈwɒ.tɚ/|[ˈwɒ.ɾɚ]|a=cot-caught}}\n*** {{audio|en|En-us-water.ogg|a=US,cot-caught}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈwɔː.tə/|[wo̞ː.tʰə]|a=RP}}\n** {{audio|e"
  body "n|En-uk-water.ogg|a=RP}}\n** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Back ache-water.wav|a=UK}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈwoː.tə/|[ˈwoː.ɾə]|a=AU,NZ}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɔːtə(ɹ)|s=2}}\n* {{hyph|en|wa|ter}}\n\n{{col-top|2|Other acce"
  body "nts and pronunciations}}\n* {{IPA|en|[ˈwoː.ʔɐ]|[ˈwoː.ʔə]|a=Estuary English}}\n* {{IPA|en|[ˈwoʊ.ʔə]|[ˈwɔo.ɾɐ]|a=Cockney}}\n* {{IPA|en|/wʊʔə/|/-ɑ/|a=MLE}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈwæ.tə/|a=Northern England,dated; "
  body "obsolete elsewhere}}, {{IPAchar|[ˈwa.tə]|[ˈwa.ɾɚ]}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈwɔ.təɾ/|a=Scotland}}, {{IPAchar|[ˈwɔ.təɾ]}}\n* {{IPA|en|[ˈwɔə.ɾə]|[ˈwɔə.ɾɚ]|a=NYC}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈwʊ.təɹ/|[ˈwʊ.ɾɚ]|a=Philadelphia,Balt"
  body "imore}}, {{enPR|wo͝otər}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈwɔɹ.təɹ/|[ˈwɔɹ.ɾɚ]|a=Western Pennsylvania}}, {{enPR|wôrtər}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈwɔː.təɹ/|[ˈwɒː.θ̠ɚ]|[ˈwɔːʔəɹ]|a=Ireland}}\n* {{IPA|en|[ˈwɔ(ː).ʈə(ɾ)]|[ˈʋɔ(ː).ʈə(ɾ)]|a"
  body "=India}}\n* {{IPA|en|[ˈʋäː.ʈ(ə)ɾ(ɯ)]|[ˈwäː.ʈ(ə)ɾ(ɯ)]|a=Tanglish}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈwoː.tə/|[ˈwɔː.tə]|a=South Africa}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈwɔ.tə/|a=SG,Malaysia}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈwɐː.t̪ɛɾ/|a=Philippines}}\n{{col-b"
  body "ottom}}\n\nThe development of the {{IPAchar|/ɔː/}} vowel is irregular and has not been conclusively explained (compare the irregular broadening of ''a'' in {{m|en|father}}).\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{ro"
  body "ot|en|ine-pro|*wed-}}\n{{etymon|en|id=liquid|:inh|enm:water<id:liquid>|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|water}}, from {{inh|en|ang|wæter|t=water}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*watar}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*wa"
  body "tōr|t=water}}, from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*wódr̥|t=water}}.\n\n{{col-top|2|cog}}\n* {{cog|sco|watter|t=water}}\n* {{cog|yol|wadher,waudher|t=water}}\n* {{cog|frr|waar,weeder,weeter,woar,woor,wååder,wåår|t="
  body "water}}\n* {{cog|stq|Woater|t=water}}\n* {{cog|fy|wetter|t=water}}\n* {{cog|cim|bassar,bazzar|t=water}}\n* {{cog|nl|water|t=water}}\n* {{cog|nds-nl|water,wotter|t=water}}\n* {{cog|de|Wasser|t=water}}\"
  body "n* {{cog|nds-de|Water,Woter|t=water}}\n* {{cog|gmw-gts|boßər,bàsser|t=water}}\n* {{cog|li|Waater,water|t=water}}\n* {{cog|lb|Waasser|t=water}}\n* {{cog|mhn|bòsser|t=water}}\n* {{cog|wym|woser|t=water}"
  body "}\n* {{cog|vls|woater|t=water}}\n* {{cog|yi|וואַסער|t=water}}\n* {{cog|da|vand|t=water}}\n* {{cog|ovd|wattn|t=water}}\n* {{cog|fo|vatn|t=water}}\n* {{cog|is|vatn|t=water}}\n* {{cog|nn|vatn|t=water}}\n"
  body "* {{cog|nb|vann|t=water}}\n* {{cog|sv|vatten|t=water}}\n* {{cog|got|𐍅𐌰𐍄𐍉|t=water}}\n* {{cog|sga|coin fodorne||otters|lit=water-dogs}}\n* {{cog|la|unda|t=wave}}\n* {{cog|lt|vanduõ|t=water}}\n* {{cog|pl"
  body "|woda|t=water}}\n* {{cog|ru|вода́|t=water}}\n* {{cog|sq|ujë|t=water}}\n* {{cog|grc|ὕδωρ|t=water}}\n* {{cog|hy|գետ|t=river}}\n* {{cog|sa|उदन्|tr=udán|t=wave, water}}\n* {{cog|hit|𒉿𒀀𒋻|tr=wa-a-tar|sc=Xsu"
  body "x|t=water}}\n{{col-bottom}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{wikidata lexeme|L3302}}\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{sid|en|Q283}} {{lb|en|uncountable}} An inorganic compound (of molecular formula {{chemf|H2O}}) found at [[r"
  body "oom temperature]] and pressure as a clear [[liquid]]; it is present naturally as [[rain#Noun|rain]], and found in [[river]]s, [[lake]]s and [[sea]]s; its solid form is [[ice#Noun|ice]] and its gaseous"
  body " form is [[steam#Noun|steam]].\n#: {{syn|en|Thesaurus:water}}\n#: {{hypo|en|ice|steam|water vapor//water vapour|;|light water|semi-heavy water|heavy water|super-heavy water}}\n#: {{mero|en|hydrogen|ox"
  body "ygen}}\n#: {{ux|en|By the action of electricity, the '''water''' was resolved into its two parts, oxygen and hydrogen.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|year=1805|month=December|author=Julius Griffiths|title=A"
  body " Journey across the Desert|journal=The Monthly Mirror|page=362\n|passage=It is wholly out of the power of language to convey any idea of the blissful enjoyment of obtaining '''water''', after an almos"
  body "t total want of it, during eight and forty hours, in the scorching regions of an Arabian desert, in the month of July.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|year=2013|month=September-October|author=[http://www.ame"
  body "ricanscientist.org/authors/detail/katie-l-burke Katie L. Burke]| magazine=w:American Scientist| url=http://www.americanscientist.org/issues/pub/2013/5/in-the-news-47|title=In the News| passage=Oxygen "
  body "levels on Earth skyrocketed 2.4 billion years ago, when cyanobacteria evolved photosynthesis: the ability to convert '''water''' and carbon dioxide into carbohydrates and waste oxygen using solar ener"
  body "gy.|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130903041000/https://www.americanscientist.org/issues/pub/2013/5/in-the-news-47}}\n## {{lb|en|uncountable|in particular}} The liquid form of this substance"
  body ": liquid {{chemf|H2O}}.\n##: {{hyper|en|liquid|fluid}}\n##: {{hypo|en|drinkwater|freshwater|meltwater|mineral water|;|hard water|soft water}}\n##: {{cot|en|ice|steam|water vapor//water vapour}}\n##: {"
  body "{ux|en|May I have a glass of '''water'''?}}\n##: {{ux|en|Your plants need more '''water'''.}}\n##* {{quote-text|en|year=1835|author=Sir {{w|John Ross (Arctic explorer)|John Ross}}; Sir {{w|James Clark"
  body " Ross}}|title=[http://books.google.com.au/books?id=SdQBAAAAYAAJ Narrative of a Second Voyage in Search of a North-west Passage &hellip;, Volume 1]|pages=284–5\n|passage=Towards the following morning, "
  body "the thermometer fell to 5°; and at daylight, there was not an atom of '''water''' to be seen in any direction.}}\n##* {{quote-book|en|year=2002|author=Arthur T. Hubbard|title=Encyclopedia of Surface a"
  body "nd Colloid Science|isbn=0824707966|page=4895\n|passage=A '''water''' drop placed on the surface of ice can either spread or form a lens depending on the properties of the three phases involved in wett"
  body "ing, i.e., on the properties of the ice, '''water''', and gas phases.}}\n##* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-05-11|volume=407|issue=8835|page=80|magazine=w:The Economist| url=http://www.economist.com/new"
  body "s/science-and-technology/21577341-worlds-third-largest-area-ice-about-undergo-systematic|title=The climate of Tibet: Pole-land| passage=Of all the transitions brought about on the Earth’s surface by t"
  body "emperature change, the melting of ice into '''water''' is the starkest. It is binary. And for the land beneath, the air above and the life around, it changes everything.|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/"
  body "RCa6m|archivedate=2023-03-10}}\n##* {{see more citations|en}}\n## {{lb|en|countable}} A [[serving#Noun|serving]] of liquid water.\n##* {{quote-book|en|year=2006|author=Lori Foster; Erin McCarthy; Amy "
  body "Garvey| title=Bad Boys of Summer| isbn=0758209347| page=91| passage=Joe bustled back and offered her a glass of wine but she shook her head. “Just a '''water''', please.”}}\n# {{lb|en|alchemy|philosop"
  body "hy}} The aforementioned liquid, considered one of the {{w|Classical elements}} or basic elements of alchemy.\n#: {{hyper|en|element}}\n#: {{cot|en|earth|air|~|wind|fire|;|wood|metal|;|void|~|ether}}\n"
  body "#: {{ux|en|He showed me the river of living '''water''', sparkling like crystal, flowing from the throne of God.}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|or|in the plural}} Water in a body; an area of [[open#Adjectiv"
  body "e|open]] water.\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Love's Labour's Lost|V|i|138|2|''Roſa.'' O vain peticioner, beg a greater matter,<br>Thou now requeſts but Mooneſhine in the '''water'''.}}\n#* {{RQ:Lincoln Pratt'"
  body "s Patients|chapter=1|passage='Twas early June, the new grass was flourishing everywheres, the posies in the yard—peonies and such—in full bloom, the sun was shining, and the '''water''' of the bay was"
  body " blue, with light green streaks where the shoal showed.}}\n#* {{RQ:NYT|author=Danny Hakim|authorlink=Danny Hakim|quotee=Kathleen B. Hogan|title=Two Misdemeanor Charges in Lake George Capsizing|archive"
  body "url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221126041035/https://www.nytimes.com/2007/02/06/nyregion/06boat.html|date=6 February 2007|passage=\""If you foresee the event and you go forward, then you are criminal"
  body "ly negligent,\"" she said, adding, \""This was a boat that navigated on the '''waters''' of Lake George since 1979. In terms of criminal negligence, there clearly wasn't the foreseeability that there ma"
  body "y be in civil negligence.\""}}\n#* '''2019''', [https://web.archive.org/web/20190311070055/https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/south-korea-proposes-rain-project-with-china-to-cut-pollution/4819207.ht"
  body "ml VOA Learning English] (public domain)\n#*: The president expressed hope that creating rain over '''waters''' between the countries would help reduce pollution.\n#: {{ux|en|And God said, Let the '''"
  body "waters''' under the heaven be gathered together unto one place, and let the dry land appear: and it was so.}}\n#: {{ux|en|The boat was found within the territorial '''waters'''.}}\n#: {{ux|en|These se"
  body "als are a common sight in the coastal '''waters''' of Chile.}}\n# {{lb|en|poetic|archaic|or|dialectal}} A [[body]] of water, almost always a [[river]], sometimes a [[lake]] or [[reservoir]], especiall"
  body "y in the names given to such bodies.\n#* {{RQ:Tyndale NT|Acts|8|36|clxvi|And as they went on their waye <br> they cam vnto a certayne '''water''' <br> and the gelded man ſayde: Se here is water <br> w"
  body "hat ſhall lett me to be baptiſed?}}\n#* {{quote-book|1=en|year=1828|author=Thomas Keightley|authorlink=Thomas Keightley|title=The Fairy Mythology|volume=I|location=London|publisher=William Harrison Ai"
  body "nsworth|page=183|passage=When the man rode off with the silver jug from the beautiful maiden, who presented it to him, an old crone set off in pursuit of him with such velocity, that she would surely "
  body "have caught him, but that providentially he came to a running '''water'''.}}\n#* {{RQ:Tennyson Poems 1842|II|Morte d’Arthur|4|On one side lay the Ocean, and on one<br>Lay a great '''water''', and the "
  body "moon was full.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|editor=William Allingham|year=1865| title=The Ballad Book: a selection of the choicest British ballads| section=William and May Margaret, or the Water of Clyde|pas"
  body "sage=But ere he came to Clyde's '''water,''' fu' loud the wind did blaw.}}\n# A combination of water and other substance(s).\n## {{lb|en|sometimes|countable}} Mineral water.\n##: {{ux|en|Perrier is th"
  body "e most popular '''water''' in this restaurant.}}\n## {{lb|en|countable|often|in the plural}} [[spa|Spa]] water; [[hot spring]]s.\n##: {{ux|en|Many people visit Bath to [[take the waters|take the '''wa"
  body "ters''']].}}\n##* {{quote-av|en|year=1942|author=w:Julius J. Epstein; w:Philip G. Epstein; {{w|Howard Koch (screenwriter)|Howard Koch}}|title={{w|Casablanca (film)|Casablanca}}|passage=Rick: My health"
  body ". I came to Casablanca for the '''waters'''.<br/>Captain Renault: The '''waters'''? What '''waters'''? We're in the desert.<br/>Rick: I was misinformed.}}\n## {{lb|en|pharmacy}} A [[solution]] in wate"
  body "r of a [[gaseous]] or readily [[volatile]] [[substance]].\n##: {{ux|en|ammonia '''water'''}}\n## A fluid in the body.\n### [[urine|Urine]]. {{defdate|from 15th c.}}\n###: {{syn|en|body fluid|bodily fl"
  body "uid|biofluid}}\n###: {{syn|en|Thesaurus:urine}}\n###* {{quote-book|en|year=1999|author=w:George R.R. Martin| title=A Clash of Kings| publisher=Bantam| year_published=2011| page=458| passage=Ser Dunave"
  body "r's squire Jodge could not hold his '''water''' when he slept.}}\n### {{sid|en|amniotic fluid}} [[amniotic fluid|Amniotic fluid]] or the [[amniotic sac]] containing it. {{qual|Used only in the plural "
  body "in the UK but often also in the singular in North America.}}\n###: {{syn|en|bag of waters}}\n###: {{ux|en|Before the child is born, the pregnant woman’s '''water''' breaks. {{qualifier|North America}}"
  body "}}\n###: {{ux|en|Before your child is born, your '''water(s)''' will break. {{qualifier|North America}}}}\n###: {{ux|en|Before the child is born, the pregnant woman’s '''waters''' break. {{qualifier|U"
  body "K}}}}\n### {{lb|en|colloquial|medicine}} A fluid that causes [[swelling]].\n###: {{ux|en|He suffers from '''water''' on the knee.}}\n# {{lb|en|business|often|attributive}} The water [[supply#Noun|supp"
  body "ly]], as a [[service]] or [[utility]].\n#: {{cot|en|electricity|internet|phone#Noun|power#Noun|sewer}}\n#: {{ux|en|The city threatened to cut off our '''water''' after we went only a month without pay"
  body "ing our bill.}}\n#: {{ux|en|Did you leave the '''water''' running again?}}\n# {{lb|en|figuratively|in the plural|or|in the singular}} A state of affairs; [[condition#Noun|condition]]s; usually with an"
  body " [[adjective]] indicating an [[adverse]] condition.\n#: {{ux|en|The rough '''waters''' of change will bring about the calm after the storm.}}\n#* {{quote-web\n|en\n|date=03/15/2026\n|title=Taiwan repo"
  body "rts large-scale Chinese military aircraft presence near island\n|work=w:Politico\n|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/QMAXK\n|source=w:Associated Press\n|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2026/03/15/taiwan"
  body "-reports-large-scale-chinese-military-aircraft-presence-near-island-00829219\n|archivedate=15 March 2026\n|text=Taiwan didn’t report any Chinese military planes that went beyond the median line and en"
  body "tered the zone for a week from Feb. 27 to March 5. After two were detected on March 6, the next four days had none. Such flights resumed in small numbers between Wednesday and Friday.<br>The drop coin"
  body "cided with the annual meeting of China’s legislature. While such flights have fallen in the past during major events and public holidays, this year’s fall was more prominent than in the past.<br>Analy"
  body "sts said the meeting could not be the sole reason behind the recent drop. Another potential factor could be a desire to calm the '''waters''' with Washington weeks before a visit by U.S. President Don"
  body "ald Trump. The White House has said that Trump would travel to China from March 31 to April 2, though Beijing has not officially confirmed that.}}\n# {{lb|en|colloquial|figuratively}} A person's [[int"
  body "uition]]. <!-- is this always in the plural?-->\n#: {{syn|en|bones}}\n#: {{ux|en|I know he'll succeed. I feel it in my '''waters'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|dated|finance}} Excess [[valuation]] of [["
  body "securities]].\n#* {{quote-journal|en| title=Too Much '''Water''' to Suit Cummins| passage=Iowa Governor Will Fight Rock Island Reorganization. He Says That Under the New Plan Too Much '''Water''' Is P"
  body "ut Into the Stock&mdash;Believes Plan Is Out of Harmony with Iowa Laws.| work=The Atlanta Constitution| date=August 2, 1902}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en| title=Says Stock ''''Water'''' Didn't Affect Fare|"
