  body "\n|watertanden\n|watertoren\n|watertrappelen\n|waterval\n|waterverf\n|waterviolier\n|watervlakte\n|watervliegtuig\n|watervogel\n|watervrees\n|watervrij\n|waterweegbree\n|waterwerk\n|waterzooi\n|waterz"
  body "uring\n|wijwater\n|woelwater\n|zeewater\n|zoet water\n|zout water\n|zwartwater\n|zwemwater\n}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|af|water}}\n* {{desc|jvd|water}}\n* {{desc|dcr|watu|water|water|waeter"
  body "}}\n* {{desc|pey|watter}}\n* {{desc|skw|water}}\n* {{desc|srn|watra|bor=1|unc=1}} {{see desc}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{nonlemma}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|nl|verb form}}\n\n# {{infl of|nl|wateren||bare"
  body "-verb}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:Van Dale online}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{l|nl|tarwe}}\n\n{{C|nl|Water}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|fr|ine-pro|*wed-}}\n{{ellipsis|fr|water-closet}"
  body "}, borrowed from {{bor|fr|en|water closet}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|watère}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Jérémy-Günther-Heinz Jähnick-water.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Somain>>)}}\n\n===Noun===\n{"
  body "{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# [[toilet]], [[bathroom]]\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|fr|toilettes}}\n* {{l|fr|toilette}} {{q|Belgium}}\n* {{l|fr|waters}}\n* {{l|fr|WC}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|fr|waters}}\n\"
  body "n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n==Hawaiian Creole==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{der+|hwc|en|water}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|hwc|noun}}\n\n# {{tcl|hwc|water|id=Q283}}\n#* {{quote-book|hwc|tlr=Josep"
  body "h Grimes|title=Da Jesus Book: Hawaii Pidgin New Testament|chapter=Matthew 8|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yKgQAQAAIAAJ|publisher=Wycliffe Bible Translators|year=2000|page=110|pageurl=https://e"
  body "bible.org/study/content/texts/hwcNT/MT8.html|ISBN=978-0-938978-21-3|text=He tell um, “Go.” So dey wen let go da guys, an go take ova da pigs. An you know wat? All da pigs wen run down one steep hill a"
  body "n fall ova da cliff inside da lake, an drown inside da '''water'''.|t=And he said unto them, Go. And they came out, and went into the swine: and behold, the whole herd rushed down the steep into the s"
  body "ea, and perished in the '''waters'''.}}\n\n==Italian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|it|ine-pro|*wed-}}\n{{pseudo-loan|it|en}}, a clipping of {{der|it|en|water closet}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{it-pr|v"
  body "àter<r:DiPI>}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{it-noun|m|#}}\n\n# [[toilet bowl]]\n# {{lb|it|colloquial}} [[water closet]], [[toilet]]\n\n===References===\n<references />\n\n==Limburgish==\n{{wp|li:}}\n\n===Alternat"
  body "ive forms===\n* {{alter|li|Waater||Eupen|Krefeld}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|li|ine-pro|*wed-}}\n{{etymon|li|id=liquid|:inh|dum:wāter<id:liquid>|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|li|dum|wāter}}, from {{inh|li|odt"
  body "|watar}}, from {{inh|li|gmw-pro|*watar}}, from {{inh|li|gem-pro|*watōr}}, from {{inh|li|ine-pro|*wódr̥}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{li-noun|g=n}}\n\n# {{l|en|water}}\n# body of water\n\n====Derived terms====\n"
  body "* {{l|li|móndjwater}}\n\n===References===\n* Stefaan Top, ''Limburgs sagenboek'' (2004), page 45\n\n==Low German==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|nds|noun}}\n\n# {{lb|nds|Drents|Twents}} {{altcase|nds|Water||w"
  body "ater}}\n\n==Middle Dutch==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|dum|ine-pro|*wed-}}\n{{etymon|dum|id=liquid|:inh|odt:watar<id:water>|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|dum|odt|watar}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|dum|/ˈw"
  body "aːtər/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{dum-noun|head=wāter|n}}\n\n# {{l|en|water}}\n\n====Inflection====\n{{dum-decl-noun-st-n|wāter}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desctree|nl|water}}\n* {{desc|li|water}}\n* {{desc"
  body "|vls|woater}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:VMNW|ID54603}}\n* {{R:MNW|70757}}\n\n{{topics|dum|Liquids}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|enm|watere|watir|waterre}}\n\n===E"
  body "tymology===\n{{root|enm|ine-pro|*wed-}}\n{{etymon|enm|id=liquid|:inh|ang:wæter<id:water>|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|enm|ang|wæter}}, from {{inh|enm|gmw-pro|*watar}}, from {{inh|enm|gem-pro|*watōr}}.\n\n===P"
  body "ronunciation===\n* {{IPA|enm|/ˈwatər/|/ˈwaːtər/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{enm-noun|pl=wateres}}\n\n# {{l|en|water}} {{gloss|liquid H<sub>2</sub>O}}\n#* {{quote-book|enm|year=c. 1190|author=Layamon|title=Brut"
  body "|edition=MS. Cotton Caligula A ix|passage=al ſwa great ſwa a beam:<br>þe he leide in ane walle ſtream.<br>Þe ilke makeð þat '''water''' hot:<br>& þan folc halwende.}}\n# {{l|en|water vapour}}, [[conde"
  body "nsation]]\n# [[lake]], [[pond]], [[ocean]], [[canal]], body of water\n# water source, [[spring]], [[well]], [[fount]]\n# [[solution]], liquid mixture\n\n====Quotations====\n* {{see citations|enm}}\n\n"
  body "====Derived terms====\n* {{l|enm|waterles}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|en|water}} {{see desc}}\n* {{desc|en-geo|watter|wetter}}\n* {{desc|sco|watter}}\n* {{desc|yol|waudher|alts=1}}\n\n====Refer"
  body "ences====\n* {{R:MED Online|entry=wā̆ter |pos=n |id=MED51881 |accessdate=2018-03-20}}\n\n{{topics|enm|Beverages|Water}}\n\n==Middle Low German==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|gml|ine-pro|*wed-}}\nFrom {{"
  body "inh|gml|osx|watar}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|gml|/ˈwaːtər/|a=originally}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|gml|noun|g=n|head=wāter}}\n\n# {{l|en|water}}\n#* {{quote-book|gml|year=1537|author=Jürgen Richo"
  body "lff the Younger|title=Datt högeste unde öldeste water recht|section=xxviii|passage=Eyn {{l|gml|schip}} effte twe effte meer liggen in einer hauen dar {{l|gml|kleine|kleyn}} '''water''' is<br>vnde plec"
  body "ht dröge {{l|gml|wēsen|tho synde}}<br>also dat dat eyne schip hart by dem andern tho liggende kumpt {{...}}|translation=A ship or two or more lie in a port with little water, which tends to be dry, so"
  body " that one the ship comes to lie close by the other {{...}}}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{gml-decl-noun|wāter|wāter|wāteres|wātere|wāter|wāter|wātere|wāteren}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|nds-de|Wate"
  body "r}}\n\n==Occitan==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|oc|ine-pro|*wed-}}\nShortened form of {{bor|oc|en|water closet}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|oc|noun|g=m}}\n\n# {{lb|oc|colloquial}} [[water closet]], [[toilet"
  body "]], [[rest room]]\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|es|en|water}}, shortening of {{m|en|water closet}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|huáter|hyph=+}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{es-noun|m|#s}}\n\n# {{a"
  body "lt sp|es|wáter}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n{{es-unadapted}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:es:DEA}}""}}"

