response_0042_api_php_action_parse_pag
  url "https://en.wiktionary.org/w/api.php?action=parse&page=yeah&prop=wikitext&formatversion=2&format=json&redirects=1"
  body "{""parse"":{""title"":""yeah"",""pageid"":4305,""redirects"":[],""wikitext"":""{{also|þeah}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{wp|yes and no}}\nColloquial form of {{m|en|yea}} or {{m|en|yes}}. Compare {"
  body "{m|en|nah}}. Analyzable as {{suffix|en|yes|h}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{IPA|en|/jɛ(ə)/|/jaː/|/jæ(.ə)/}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-yeah.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-yeah-interjection.ogg|a=US|pos=in"
  body "terjection}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɛə|ɛ|æ|s=1}}\n\n====Particle====\n{{en-head|pcl}} {{tlb|en|colloquial}}\n\n# {{cap|yes}}.\n#: {{syn|en|yes|yep|yup|aye|ya|yea|uh-huh|Thesaurus:yes}}\n#: {{ux|en|&mdash;You "
  body "wanna get pizza for dinner? &mdash;'''Yeah''', all right.}}\n# {{n-g|Used to express [[acknowledgment]] of what was previously said.}}\n#: {{ux|en|&mdash;You wanna get pizza for dinner? &mdash;'''Yeah"
  body "''', I think I'm gonna have leftovers instead.}}\n# {{n-g|Used to ascertain the continued [[attention]] of the listener.}}\n#: {{syn|en|eh<qq:Canada>}}\n#: {{ux|en|I was walking down the road, '''yeah"
  body "''', and you know what I saw, '''yeah'''? A dog wearing a dress!}}\n\n=====Usage notes=====\n* The particle for ascertaining attention may be proscribed.\n\n=====Alternative forms=====\n* {{alt|en|yea"
  body "}}\n* {{alt|en|ya}}\n* {{alt|en|ye||Internet}}, {{alt|en|yeh}}\n* {{alt|en|yeag||internet slang|humorous}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col3|en|heck yeah|hells yeah|aww yeah|fuck yeah|oh yeah|shit ye"
  body "ah|yeah-nah|yeah way|yeah-huh|hell yeah|I will yeah|yeah, no|yee}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n* {{l|en|ya}}, {{l|en|yah}}, {{l|en|ja}}\n* {{l|en|yea}}\n* {{l|en|yay||yes}}\n* {{l|en|yeh}}\n* {{l|en|y"
  body "es}}\n* {{l|en|yas}}, {{l|en|yass}}\n* {{l|en|yuh}}\n* {{l|en|ye}}\n* {{l|en|Y}}, {{l|en|y}}\n* {{l|en|yee}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n* ''Note: Many languages have no exact equivalent of this word; "
  body "in those cases, the translations given here are for'' '''yes'''.\n{{trans-top|yes}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t|az|həri}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|sí}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|是啊|tr=shì a}}, {{t|cmn|[[對"
  body "]][[啊]]|tr=duì a}}, {{t+|cmn|啊|tr=à}}, {{t+|cmn|嗯|tr=ǹg}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|jo}}, {{t+|cs|no}} <!-- Yes, this is in the right place, \""no\"" means \""yeah\"" or \""yep\"" in Czech, Slovak, Polish -->\n* Du"
  body "tch: {{t+|nl|ja}}, {{t+|nl|jawel}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|joo}}, {{t+|fi|juu}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|ouais}}\n* German: {{qualifier|yeah}} {{t+|de|jo}}, {{t+|de|joa}}; {{qualifier|yes}} {{t+|de|ja}}\n* Gree"
  body "k: {{t+|el|ναι}}\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|כע|tr=ke}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|हाँ}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|igen}}, {{t+|hu|ja}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|já}}\n* Interlingua: {{t+|ia|si}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|sì}}, {{t+|"
  body "it|già}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|うん|tr=un}}, {{t+|ja|そう|tr=sō}}, {{t+|ja|ええ|tr=ē}}, {{t+|ja|ああ|tr=ā}}\n* Kapampangan: {{t|pam|awa}}, {{t|pam|uwa}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|응}}, {{t+|ko|네}}, {{t+|ko|예}}, {{t+|k"
  body "o|응}}, {{t+|ko|어}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t+|lt|taip}}, {{t+|lt|jo}}\n* Louisiana Creole: {{t|lou|wé}}\n* Navajo: {{t|nv|wehee}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t+|nb|ja}}, {{t|nb|yeah}}, {{t+|nb|ja vel}}\n*: N"
  body "ynorsk: {{t+|nn|ja}}, {{t|nn|yeah}}, {{t|nn|ja vel}}\n* Occitan: {{t+|oc|òc}}\n* Old Church Slavonic: {{t|cu|ⰵⰹ}}\n* Persian:\n*: Dari: {{t+|prs|آه}}, {{t|prs|بَلی}},  {{t+|prs|آری}}\n*: Iranian Persi"
  body "an: {{t+|fa-ira|بله|tr=bale}}, {{t+|fa-ira|آره|tr=âre}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|tak}}, {{t+|pl|no}}<!-- Yes, this is in the right place, \""no\"" means \""yeah\"" or \""yep\"" in Czech, Slovak, Polish -->, {{t+|"
  body "pl|aha|m}},  {{t+|pl|ta|m}} {{qualifier|colloquial}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|sim}}, {{t+|pt|é}}, {{t+|pt|iá}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|da}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|ага́}}, {{t+|ru|ага́|t"
  body "r=ahá}}, {{t+|ru|угу́}}, {{t+|ru|угу́|tr=uhú}}, {{t+|ru|так}}, {{t+|ru|ну}}\n* Serbo-Croatian: {{t+|sh|da}} {{t+|sh|da}}\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|да̑}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|dȃ}}\n* Sicilian: {{t+|scn|sì}}, "
  body "{{t+|scn|sè}}, {{t|scn|certu}}\n* Slovak: {{t+|sk|no}} <!-- Yes, this is in the right place, \""no\"" means \""yeah\"" or \""yep\"" in Czech, Slovak, Polish -->, {{t|sk|hej}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|ja}}\n* Spa"
  body "nish: {{t+|es|sí}}, {{t|es|seh}}, {{t+|es|sipi}}, {{t+|es|aa}}, {{t+|es|mm}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|ja|n}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|เออ}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|еге́}}, {{t+|uk|та}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|ہاں|tr=hā̃}} {{"
  body "qualifier|informal}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|ừ}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t+|vi|ờ}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|si}}\n* Welsh: {{t|cy|iah}}\n* Yoruba: {{t|yo|bẹ́ẹ̀ ni}}\n{{trans-bottom}"
  body "}\n\n====Interjection====\n{{en-intj}}\n\n# {{n-g|Expressing [[joy]], [[celebration]], [[glee]], etc.}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''Yeah!''' We did it!}}\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n* {{l|en|hurrah}}, {{l|en|hurray}}, "
  body "{{l|en|woohoo}}, {{l|en|yay}}, {{l|en|yippee}}<!--etc-->\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col3|en|yeah right}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|expressing joy}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|yes}}, {{t+|nl|jip"
  body "pie}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|jee}}, {{t+|fi|joo}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|ouais}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|sì}}, {{t+|it|vai}}, {{t+|it|evvai}}, {{t|it|evviva}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|やった|tr=yatta}}, {{t|ja|イェー}} {{"
  body "qualifier|slang}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|아싸}}, {{t|ko|앗싸}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|é!}}, {{t|pt|isso aí!}} (Brazil), {{t|pt|boa!}} (Portugal)\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|да!}}, {{t+|ru|ура́!}}, {{t|ru|э-ге́й!}}, {"
  body "{t+|ru|е!}} {{qualifier|slang}}\n* Sicilian: {{t|scn|forza ḍḍocu!}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|так!}}, {{t+|uk|та!}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====See also====\n{{col3|en|yes}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nSee [[year]"
  body "].\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{pronunciation spelling of|en|year}}.\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aehy|Haye|haye|heya}}\n\n{{cln|en|heteronyms}}\n\n==Chinese==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{rfe"
  body "|zh|From English?}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{zh-pron\n|c=je1\n|cat=n,v,a\n}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|zh|noun}}\n\n# {{tcl|zh|V sign|id=peace|lb=HKC}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{zh-l|V字手勢}}\n\n===Verb===\"
  body "n{{head|zh|verb}}\n\n# {{lb|zh|Hong Kong Cantonese}} to [[make]] a [[V sign]]\n\n===Adjective===\n{{head|zh|adjective}}\n\n# {{lb|zh|Hong Kong Cantonese|somewhat|dated}} [[cool]]; [[stylish]]""}}"

