  body " Winnebago: {{t|win|hąąhąʼa}}\n* Wiradjuri: {{t|wrh|ngawa}}\n* Woiwurrung: {{t|wyi|ngai}}\n* Wolof: {{t+|wo|waaw}},  {{t|wo|waawaaw}}\n* Xhosa: {{t|xh|ewe}}\n* Yaghnobi: {{t|yai|ҳа}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|y"
  body "i|יאָ}}\n* Yoruba: {{t|yo|bẹ́ẹ̀ ni}},  {{t|yo|bẹ́ẹ̀ náà ni}},  {{t|yo|hẹn (informal)}}\n* Yup'ik: {{t|esu|ii-i}}\n* Zazaki: {{t+|zza|e}}\n* Zulu: {{t+|zu|yebo}}\n* ǃXóõ: {{t|nmn|ʻée}},  {{t|nmn|ʻíi}},"
  body "  {{t|nmn|ʻē êh}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|word used to indicate disagreement or dissent in reply to a negative statement}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|بَلَى}}\n*: South Levantine Arabic: {{t|ajp|مبلا|t"
  body "r=mbala}}\n* Breton: {{t+|br|geo}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|sí}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|jo}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|jawel}},  {{t+|nl|toch}}, {{qualifier|most common form}}  {{t+|nl|wel}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|ikka}"
  body "}\n* Faroese: {{t|fo|jú}},  {{t|fo|júgv}}\n* Fijian: {{t+|fj|ia}},  {{t+|fj|io}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|''verb'' + [[-pas]]}},  {{t+|fi|kylläpäs}},  {{t+|fi|joopas}} {{q|colloquial}},  {{t+|fi|juupas}} {{"
  body "q|colloquial}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|si}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|კი}}\n* German: {{t+|de|doch}},  {{t+|de|wohl}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|ναι}}\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|דווקא כן|tr=dávka (dáfka, colloquial) kén}}\n* Hung"
  body "arian: {{t|hu|de igen}},  {{t+|hu|de}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|jú}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|sì}},  {{t|it|invece sì}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|いいえ|tr=īe}}\n* Kapampangan: {{t|pam|alina}},  {{t|pam|aliman}},  {{"
  body "t|pam|aliya}},  {{t|pam|ua}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|아니요}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|immō}},  {{t|la|immō vērō}}\n* Norwegian: {{t+|no|jo}}\n* Pashto: {{t+|ps|هو|tr=ho}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|چرا|tr=čerâ}}\n* Polish"
  body ": {{t|pl|ależ tak}},  {{t+|pl|owszem}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|sim}}\n* Romanian: {{t|ro|ba da}}\n* Romansh: {{qualifier|Rumantsch Grischun, Vallader}}  {{t|rm|bain}}, {{qualifier|Sursilvan}}  {{t|rm|b"
  body "ein}}, {{qualifier|Sutsilvan}}  {{t|rm|bagn}}, {{qualifier|Surmiran}}  {{t|rm|gea bagn}}, {{qualifier|Puter, Vallader}}  {{t|rm|bainschi}}, {{qualifier|Puter, Vallader}}  {{t|rm|bainschi hei}}, {{qual"
  body "ifier|Vallader}}  {{t|rm|bainschi hai}}\n* Russian: {{t|ru|ещё как}},  {{t+|ru|наоборо́т}},  {{t+|ru|напро́тив}}\n* Sicilian: {{t|scn|se}},  {{t|scn|e mmeci se}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|dà}},  {{t+|sl|já}"
  body "}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|sí}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|jo}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|தான்}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t|vi|có chứ}} {{qualifier|in response to a statement containing ''không có''}},  {{t|vi|được chứ}} {{quali"
  body "fier|in response to a statement containing ''không được''}}\n* Walloon: {{t+|wa|siya}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Alabama: {{t-check|akz|yamá}}, {{t-check|akz|yamma}}\n* Albanian: {{t+"
  body "check|sq|po}}\n* Arabic: {{t+check|ar|أَجَل}}\n* Aymara: {{t+check|ay|jisa}}\n* Breton: {{qualifier|1}} {{t+check|br|ya}}, {{t+check|br|eo}}, {{qualifier|2}} {{t+check|br|geo}}\n* Chickasaw: {{t-check"
  body "|cic|hohmi}}, {{t-check|cic|ah}}\n* Garifuna: {{qualifier|used by males}} {{t-check|cab|ayé}}, {{qualifier|used by females}} {{t-check|cab|ayí}}\n* Guarani:\n*: Paraguayan Guarani: {{t-check|gug|heẽ}}"
  body "\n* Inuktitut: {{t+check|iu|ᐄ}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{t+check|ckb|ئا}}, {{t-check|ckb|بەڵێ}}\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t+check|kmr|belê}}, {{t+check|kmr|erê}}, {{t+check|kmr|a}}, {{t+check|"
  body "kmr|e}}\n* Maguindanao: {{t-check|mdh|wai}}\n* Malagasy: {{t+check|mg|eny}}\n* Maléku Jaíka: {{t-check|gut|áo}}\n* Sardinian: {{t-check|sc|eja}}\n* Serbo-Croatian: {{t-check|sh|да}} {{t+check|sh|da}}\"
  body "n* Sinhalese: {{t-check|si|ඔවු}}\n* Swahili: {{t+check|sw|ndiyo}}, {{t+check|sw|sawa}}\n* Tausug: {{t-check|tsg|huun}}\n* Tz'utujil: {{t-check|tzj|ken}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n}}<!-- close {{multitrans}} "
  body "-->\n\n===Interjection===\n{{en-intj}}\n\n# {{ng|An exclamation of pleasure or approval, usually transcribed with an exclamation point.}}\n#: {{ant|en|no}}\n#: {{ux|en|Our second goal of the match! ''"
  body "'Yes'''!}}\n# {{ng|Response that confirms that the user is paying attention.}}\n# {{lb|en|interrogative}} {{ng|Used to ask for more information with a request.}}\n#: {{ux|en|I need some help.<br>'''Ye"
  body "s'''?}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{multitrans|data=\n{{trans-top-also|expression of pleasure, joy or great excitement|yay|whoo|yippee}}\n* Breton: {{t+|br|ya}}\n* Choctaw: {{t|cho|a̱}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|"
  body "nl|ja}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|jes}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|jes|alt=jes!}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|oui}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|ურა}},  {{t|ka|ვაშა}}\n* German: {{t+|de|ja}}\n* Gothic: {{t|got|𐌾𐌰}}\n* Greek: {{t+"
  body "|el|ναι|n}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|יש!|tr=yesh!}}\n* Irish: {{t+|ga|sea}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|sì}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|よし|tr=yoshi}},  {{t+|ja|やった|tr=yatta}}\n* Kapampangan: {{t|pam|ayua}},  {{t|pam|ayua"
  body "naman}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|sīc}},  {{t+|la|eu}},  {{t|la|euge}},  {{t|la|iō}}\n* Mari:\n*: Eastern Mari: {{t|mhr|ыгы}}\n* Norwegian: {{t+|no|yes|n}}\n* Old English: {{t|ang|gea}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|tak}"
  body "}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|sim!}},  {{t+|pt|é!}},  {{t+|pt|assim!}},  {{t+|pt|isso!}},  {{t+|pt|aí!}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|да}}!\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|tha}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Latin: {{t|sh|to!}"
  body "}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|to!}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|sí}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|ja}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|evet}}\n* Welsh: {{t|cy|ie'n}}\n* Wiradjuri: {{t|wrh|yaala!}},  {{t|wrh|yalu}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n{{tr"
  body "ans-top|response that confirms attention}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|niin}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|はい|tr=hai}}\n* Kapampangan: {{t|pam|wa}},  {{t|pam|o}},  {{t|pam|opu}}\n* Nepali: {{t|ne|हजुर}}\n* Spanish: {"
  body "{t|es|dí}}\n* Sundanese: {{t|su|kulan}}, {{t|su|kah}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|vâng}} {{qualifier|Northern Vietnam}},  {{t+|vi|dạ}} {{qualifier|Southern Vietnam}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n{{trans-top|response"
  body " that asks for more information about a request}}\n* Spanish: {{t|es|dí}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|ம்ம்}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|vâng}} {{qualifier|Northern Vietnam}},  {{t+|vi|dạ}} {{qualifier|Southern Viet"
  body "nam}},  {{t+|vi|ơi}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n}}<!-- close {{multitrans}} -->\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|+|yesses}}\n\n# An affirmative expression; an answer that shows agreement or acc"
  body "eptance.\n#: {{syn|en|aye|yea|nod}}\n#: {{ant|en|no|nay}}\n#: {{ux|en|Was that a '''yes'''?}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1913|author={{w|Edgar Rice Burroughs}}|title={{w|The Return of Tarzan}}|publisher"
  body "=Ballantine Books|location=New York|year_published=1963|page=121|passage=Yet a woman’s “'''yes'''” would have bound him to that other life forever, and made the thought of this savage existence repuls"
  body "ive.}}\n# A vote of support or in favor of something.\n#: {{syn|en|aye|yea}}\n#: {{ant|en|nay|no}}\n#: {{ux|en|The workers voted on whether to strike, and there were thirty \""'''yeses'''\"" and one \""n"
  body "o\"".}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{multitrans|data=\n{{trans-top|answer that shows agreement or acceptance}}\n* Arabic: {{t+|ar|نَعَم|f}},  {{t|ar|نَعَمَانِ|f-d}},  {{t+|ar|نَعَمَات|f-p}}\n* Basque: {{"
  body "t|eu|baietz}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|同意}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|ano}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|ja}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|jeso}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|kyllä}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|oui|m}},  {{t+|fr|si|m"
  body "}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|თანხმობა}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Ja|m|n}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|ναι|n}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|sì|m}}\n* Norwegian: {{t+|no|ja|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|sim|m}},  {{t+|pt|afirmativo|m}}\"
  body "n* Russian: {{t+|ru|да|m}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|dà|m}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|sí|m}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|ja}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|ஆம்}}, {{t+|ta|ஆமாம்}}\n* Yoruba: {{t|yo|òòò}},  {{t|yo|ẹyi}} {{qualifier|ho"
  body "norific}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|vote of support}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t|cmn|同意票}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|jaa}},  {{t+|fi|kyllä}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|oui|m}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|კი}}\n* "
  body "German: {{t+|de|Ja|n}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|ναι|n}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|sì|m}},  {{t|it|voto a favore|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|sim|m}},  {{t+|pt|a favor|m}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|sí|m}},  {{t|es|a favor|"
  body "m}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|ja}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|ஆம்}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n}}<!-- close {{multitrans}} -->\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb|~es,~ses}}\n\n# {{lb|en|colloquial|transitive}} To agree with, [[affirm"
  body "]], [[approve]].\n#: {{syn|en|agree|consent|nod}}\n#: {{ux|en|Did he '''yes''' the veto?}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|year= 1972|month= Oct|author= John Barth|title= Perseid|volume=|issue=|page= 79|magazi"
  body "ne= Harper's Magazine|publisher=|issn=|url=|passage=\""That's really what you wanted?\"" I '''yessed''' both; ...}}\n# {{lb|en|colloquial|intransitive}} To say {{m-g|yes}}.\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2"
  body "5 February 1923|title=Going Up!|journal=[[w:Lincoln Journal Star|Sunday State Journal]]|location=Lincoln, Neb.|page=!12—B|pageurl=https://www.newspapers.com/newspage/334843666/|column=2|issn=1054-7975"
  body "|oclc=1037545322|passage=The next day another writer asked us: “Didja hear about So-and-So? Got two hundred and fifty bucks for an idea!” We “'''yessed'''” and went our way.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year"
  body "=1994|author=Malcolm Ross|chapter=Part Three: The New Woman|title=Kernow & Daughter|location=London|publisher=[[w:Book Club Associates|BCA]]|page=293|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/kernowdaughter"
  body "0000ross/page/293/mode/1up|isbn=9780749902629|passage=“Heaven knows why a woman ‘Noes’!” / Clarrie nodded glumly. “And why she ‘'''Yesses'''’ in the end.”}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2005|author=Tyree "
  body "Campbell|chapter=11|title=Nyx|location=Cedar Rapids, Ia.|publisher=Sam’s Dot Publishing|page=93|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9781930847699/page/93/mode/1up|passage=\""{{...|nospace=1}} Are "
  body "you—?\"" / \"".&nbsp;.&nbsp;. all right?\"" / We '''yessed''' simultaneously. / \""At least, I think so.\""}}\n# {{lb|en|slang}} To attempt to [[flatter]] someone by habitually [[agreeing]]\n\n====Derived "
  body "terms====\n* {{l|en|yes to death}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{multitrans|data=\n{{trans-top|to affirm}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|beamen}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|jesi}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|vahvistaa}}\n* German"
  body ": {{t+|de|bejahen}}\n* Gujarati: {{t|gu|હા પાડવી}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|approvare}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|aceptar}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|godkänna}},  {{t+|sv|acceptera}}\n* Tamil: {{t|ta|ஒப்புதலளி}}\n{{tr"
  body "ans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|attempt to flatter by agreeing}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|myönnellä}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|подда́кивать|impf}}, {{t+|ru|подда́кнуть|pf}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|de acuerdo}}\n{{trans"
  body "-bottom}}\n}}<!-- close {{multitrans}} -->\n\n===Determiner===\n{{head|en|determiner}}\n\n# {{lb|en|humorous}} {{n-g|[[counter#Verb|Countering]] a [[statement]] using the {{glossary|determiner}} {{m|e"
  body "n|no#Determiner}}:}}\n## [[there be|There is]]; {{n-g|indicating the [[existence]] of something.}}\n##* {{quote-newsgroup|en|date=9 July 1997|author=Marky J|title=No Games?<!--sic--> … '''Yes''' games"
  body "!!|newsgroup=rec.games.video.nintendo|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20251205121852/https://groups.google.com/g/rec.games.video.nintendo/c/oDWp9fKevvI/m/eLks6RyLBHwJ|passage=Have you heard thi"
  body "s before? \""Nintendo 64 has no games!\"" Well, I did a little researching, and here's what I found: {{...}}}}\n##* {{quote-newsgroup|en|date=15 December 1997|author={{=}}^.^{{=}}|title=No water...|news"
  body "group=alt.home.repair|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20251205122044/https://groups.google.com/g/alt.home.repair/c/-nWbbPg82Uc/m/8eWagZDOkL8J|passage={{quote-gloss|Message header:}} No water..."
  body " '''YES''' WATER! / We have water again!}}\n##* {{quote-newsgroup|en|date=26 February 2003|author=jack|title=discussion|newsgroup=ne.weather|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20260131063031/https"
  body "://groups.google.com/g/ne.weather/c/9euSQSKt9QA/m/CCK4U5RERrQJ|passage=>> What a silly question, you, momma and the cats.<br>><br>> No cats and she's off-topic here, pest.<br>'''Yes''' cats 4 of them "
  body "to be exact.}}\n##* {{quote-newsgroup|en|date=1 December 2005|author=shadow|title=Christians in alt.atheism are going to HELL|newsgroup=alt.atheism|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/2025120512145"
  body "0/https://groups.google.com/g/alt.atheism/c/B9UeBYI3PCQ/m/kn0nqVlMfsgJ|passage=> >sure. try faking it. you better be good at it, atheist.<br>><br>> No need Christian.<br>'''yes''' need atheist.}}\n## "
  body "{{n-g|Indicating the [[possibility]] or [[allowance]] of something.}}\n##* {{quote-journal|en|year=1973|author=[[w:William Stafford (poet)|William Stafford]]|title=Having Become a Writer: Some Reflect"
  body "ions|journal=[[w:University of Oregon media#Northwest Review|Northwest Review]]|volume=XIII|location=Eugene, Ore.|publisher=w:University of Oregon|page=91|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=D1B"
  body "ZAAAAIAAJ&q=%22yes+parking%22|issn=0029-3423|oclc=1760710|passage=When our family left graduate school, it was in a cocoon of our own feelings, with college life behind us and the boys excitedly talki"
  body "ng about what was “behead of us,” and our car avoiding no parking signs but aiming for “'''yes''' parking.”}}\n##* {{quote-newsgroup|en|date=1 February 2000|author=Fulmination|title=Brier|newsgroup=re"
  body "c.pets.dogs.behavior|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20260131062210/https://groups.google.com/g/rec.pets.dogs.behavior/c/tVV49yVl-lQ/m/htQnJI2NbicJ|passage=I lived in a no-pets apartment in a h"
  body "ouse. And my boyfriend and I broke up (that's another installment, too!), and I grabbed the dog, who was always mine, anyway. And my landlord agreed that it was a '''yes'''-pets apartment shortly afte"
  body "rward.}}\n##* {{RQ:NYT|date=11 November 2010|author=w:Adam Nagourney|title=Las Vegas Casinos Are a Last Bastion for Smokers|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111019235253/https://www.nytimes.co"
  body "m/2010/11/12/us/12smoke.html|passage=Smoking is banned in restaurants, shops, public hallways and other nongambling parts of casinos; yet it is hard to tell where the no-smoking area ends and the '''y"
  body "es'''-smoking area begins.}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|yes homo|yes way}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|en|yee}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=esy|Sey.|Sye|eys|sye}}\n\n{{cln|en|phrasebook|"
  body "responses|3-letter words}}\n\n==Ahtna==\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom the root {{m|aht|yaats||to snow}}, and related to the noun {{m|aht|yaas||falling snow}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|aht|noun|cat2=d-gend"
  body "er nouns}}\n\n# [[snow]] on the ground\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|aht|yesbaa||snowy owl}}\n* {{l|aht|yesdayaał||he/she is wading in the snow}}\n* {{l|aht|yes tlʼigeʼ||snow flea}}\n\n====Stem==="
  body "=\n{{head|aht|stem}}\n\n# ''Verbal stem occurring in the following root, aspect, and mode combinations'':\n#: {{aht-stem-set-header|indent}}\n{{aht-stem-set-row2|mom|||{{l|aht|yaats}} (snow)|}}\n|}\n\"
  body "n===Etymology 2===\nRelated to {{m|aht|ses||safety}}, {{m|aht|-yiitsʼ||breath}}, and {{m|aht|-yiigeʼ||spirit}}.\n\n====Root====\n{{head|aht|root}}\n\n# to [[escape]], [[evade]], become [[safe]]\n\n==="
  body "==Stem set=====\n{{aht-stem-set-header}}\n{{aht-stem-set-row|conc|yes|yes|yes|yes}}\n{{aht-stem-set-row|con-cus|yiis|yiis|yiis|yiis}}\n{{aht-stem-set-footer}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col2|aht\n|"
  body "sdyes<t:he/she is safe>\n|ukʼedezyesi<t:wind-dried meat>\n}}\n\n===References===\n* {{Kari|page=438}}\n\n==Asturian==\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|ast|verb form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|ast|ser||2|s|pres|indc}"
  body "}\n\n==Coatepec Nahuatl==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|naz|noun}}\n\n# [[blood]]\n\n==Danish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|da|en|yes}}.\n\n===Interjection===\n{{head|da|intj}}\n\n# {{lb|da|colloquial}} {{ng|E"
  body "xpression of triumph, vehement approval, etc.}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|nl|en|yes}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/jɛs/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-yes.ogg}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|yes}}\n* "
  body "{{rhymes|nl|ɛs|s=1}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{head|nl|interjection}}\n\n# {{lb|nl|colloquial}} [[yay]] {{gloss|exclamation of happiness or enthusiasm}}\n#: {{syn|nl|joepie|jippie|hoezee <q:archaic>|jo"
  body "echei <q:archaic>}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|fr|:bor|en:yes}}\n{{bor+|fr|en|yes}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|yèss}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-LoquaxFR-yes.wav|a=<<France>> (<"
  body "<Vosges>>)}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{fr-intj}}\n\n# {{lb|fr|chiefly|North America|colloquial}} [[yes]]!\n#: {{syn|fr|oui}}\n\n==Ido==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|io|eo|jes}}, from {{der|io|en|yes}"
  body "}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|io|/jes/}}\n\n===Adverb===\n{{head|io|adverb}}\n\n# {{l|en|yes}}\n#: {{ant|io|no}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n\n====Noun====\n{{enm-noun|-}}\n\n# {{"
  body "alt form|enm|is||ice|id=ice}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n\n====Interjection====\n{{head|enm|interjection}}\n\n# {{alt form|enm|yis||yes}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\n\n====Determiner====\n{{head|enm|determiner}}"
  body "\n\n# {{lb|enm|East Anglian}} {{alt form|enm|þes||these}}\n\n===Etymology 4===\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|enm|noun form}}\n\n# {{lb|enm|Late ME}} {{plural of|enm|ye||eye}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n\n===Etymolo"
  body "gy===\n{{ubor|pt|en|yes}}. {{doublet|pt|iá}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pt-IPA|iés}}\n* {{rhyme|pt|ɛs|ɛjs|s=1}}\n* {{hyph|pt|yes}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{head|pt|interjection|head=!}}\n\n# {{lb|pt|c"
  body "olloquial}} {{l|en|yes}}; [[yeah]]; {{ng|expression of pleasure, joy or great excitement}}\n#: {{syn|pt|isso!}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{ubor|es|en|yes}"
  body "}.\n\n====Interjection====\n{{head|es|interjection}}\n\n# {{lb|es|colloquial}} {{l|en|yes}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{nonlemma}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|es|noun form|g=f-p}}\n\n# {{noun form of|es|ye||p"
  body "}}\n\n==Swedish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|sv|en|yes}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|sv|/jɛs/}}\n* {{rhymes|sv|ɛsː|s=1}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{head|sv|interjection}}\n\n# {{lb|sv|colloquial}} "
  body "{{l|en|yes|}}\n#: {{ux|sv|'''Yes''', det stämmer|'''Yep''', that's correct}}\n#: {{ux|sv|'''Yes'''! Där satt den! Rätt upp i krysset.|'''Yes'''! Nailed it! [\""There (just now) it sat!\"" (where I wante"
